description: Sara talks to Irons and we get a look inside Level 42.
Sara Pezzini gets to watch over Jackie Estacado transfer to safehouse, which don't go as planned as Jackie is kidnapped.
name: Witchblade/The Darkness, Part 1

description: Back from her foray into the Underworld, Sara emerges with FULL power over the Witchblade. Just in time, too, because she has unknowingly brought back several wicked creatures who are ready to take a bite out of the Big Apple--creatures who embody the world's most deadly serial killers and flesh eaters! Sara must hunt these vile creatures down--but she can't do it alone! Who can help Sara stop these abominations?

Things really heat up as detective Sara Pezzini attempts to keep the unknowingly released Demons of the Underworld from wreaking havoc on the city! In her quest to stop them, Sara encounters an ancient clan, out to destroy the demons with the use of some amazing powers unknown to mortal men! Will Sara be able to embrace these strange new powers in order to become the warrior she has always dreamed of? Plus, Sara uses the Witchblade with many surprising results--even to her!

With the help of her new allies and the full power of the Witchblade, Sara makes her final attempt to banish the creatures back to the underworld from where they came. Plus, one of those new allies holds a very special link to Sara’s past, one that will change her life forever!

The dawn of a new era for Witchblade begins, as penciling sensation Keu Cha (Rising Stars) becomes the ongoing artist for everyone’s favorite gauntlet wielding detective. Plus, the new writing team of Rick Veitch and Paul Jenkins (Inhumans, Spawn, Hulk) start to weave a tale that will explore untold history of the Witchblade and alter the course of Sara’s life forever! Events from this mystic and gypsy filled issue will set the path for Paul Jenkins to take over as full time writer with issue #43! Bear witness to the changing of the guard as Top Cow’s longest running series sets its sights on becoming the most promising storyline of the new millennium.

The most promising new story line of the new millennium continues as Sara attempts to deal with the ramifications of last issue. Rick Veitch and Paul Jenkins have provided nothing short of a stellar new direction for everyone’s favorite Witchblade wielding detective and new series artist Keu Cha has exemplified the ability to fill Sara’s world with unique and explosive visuals. Now is the time to pick up Witchblade and find out what everyone has been talking about!

Sara PEZzini’s got some serious problems. She’s starting to wonder if she’s really in control of the Witchblade, all the while trying to keep quiet the voices she keeps hearing in her head. And as if Sara’s world wasn’t unreal enough, someone’s got the hots for her and is leaving PEZ dispensers in the most unusual of places to let her know. This is the debut of Paul Jenkins’ story arc, and with all the surprises he has in store, you’ll wanna be there from the start.
name: A Cold Day In Hell

description: The investigation of the "Impossible Murders" continues. The stress of finding out who's responsible for these killings is really beginning to take a toll on Sara. To make things worse, she wakes one day to find the Witchblade trying to overcome her as if the Witchblade is feeding on her. Yikes!
name: Single Bullet Theory

description: Sara Pezzini continues her communications with Logon via the Internet. When will she finally get to meet him in person? As Sara interrogates a witness, she gets called about another body being discovered. When the body is dug up, Sara is shocked to see who the victim is. As a matter of fact, the murder seems like an impossibility. Why? You'll have to read Witchblade 44 to find out. You're in for a shock too!
name: Bang

description: Sara Pezzini, hot on the trail of the Pez serial murderer, is being given more clues than she knows what to do with. However, none of these will help her find the killer as much as an old painting she finds at the location of the latest murder. Only by accepting the Witchblade's help, it seems, can Sara tap into the inspiration of the artist and in so doing, journey into the mind of the psychopath who is one step ahead of her at every turn. But what sacrifice will the Witchblade ask for in return?
name: Firing Line

description: An old lesson learned anew: the devil must have his due. Sara begins to discover that each time the Witchblade is brought into play, it devours a little piece of her soul. Detective Pezzini must struggle with her emotions -- literally! -- as paramedics and doctors rush to save the life of her partner. It's a time to hope and a time to pray, but who is going to listen to her prayers? Only the Witchblade can hear her, but will its offer of assistance come with too high a price?

An affluent and influential family -- two children, two suicides. As a distraught mother and father try to contain their grief, Sara Pezzini listens to the voices of the Witchblade in order to uncover the truth. And what she finds will shock even the most hardened NYPD detective - hidden somewhere in the muttering sounds of the ancient blade are the voices of two children who have been crying out to be heard for many years. It's a cry that's gone unnoticed, both in life and in death -- until now.

Sara Pezzini returns to the business of detective work, hoping to gather enough evidence against the Impossible Killer to convict. But her life becomes all the more complicated with the return of an old foe who is hotter than ever before. There must be a way to stand against these adversaries... but is Sara willing to accept her place in the society of the supernatural without protest? And how much will the Witchblade ask for in return?

Variant editions w/same cover in gold foil and red foil from Dynamic Forces (also available signed)

The Witchblade tricked Sara into sacrificing her last partner, Blake whom she was teamed up with to stop the MELT DOWN OF NEW YORK CITY. Although they managed to stop the terrorist, Sara was devastated by the loss of her partner. Now it seems the FIRESTARTER, like the Phoenix has risen from the ashes and returned to finish the job. Will Sara trust the Witchblade this time? She may not have another choice. This THRILLING issue written by series scribe and fan-favorite PAUL JENKINS will lead into issue 50 which brings many changes to the Witchblade storyline as we know it. Don't get left behind!

Note: Though Keu Cha is given a credit on the cover, he didn't work on this issue at all.

Top Cow's flagship title reaches its 50th issue and the Witchblade will never be the same again! Sara is given a clue as to the true nature of the Witchblade as she is brought into the confidence of an ages-old Masonic group who are preparing for what they believe is Armageddon. In this special anniversary issue, readers will finally be given a clue as to the true origin and intent of the Witchblade, PLUS, one of Sara's old friends makes his return!
Introducing the creepiest hero in the Marvel Universe as Rick Sheridan's life unravels thanks to the mysterious alien known as the Sleepwalker.
name: To Sleep Perchance to Scream!

description: Young Rick discovers that Sleepwalker, the other-dimensional hero trapped in his mind, is indeed real --- but can't decide whether he's friend or foe!  Plus, Sleepwalker faces his first super-villian, 8-Ball!
name: Behind The 8-Ball
You Can't Tell A Bookworm By It's Cover

description:
An Infinity Gauntlet crossover!  Spider-Man concludes his two-issue guest-appearance as Sleepwalker is draw into part one of a three-part Infinity Gauntlet storyline.               

Editor's Note(Blue_Shield): In the original solicitation(above) this was to be part of a multi-issue Infinity Gauntlet arc, but issue #7, became the only IG crossover.
name: Web Of Confusion (Part 2)

description: An Infinity Gauntlet Crossover
name: The Ties That Bind!

description: Guest-starring Deathlok! At a House Of Horrors, Sleepwalkerand Deathlokdiscovers two horrors --- each other!
name: Night Of The Living Deathlok!

description:
Introducing Lullabye, the lethally lovely villianess whose soothing songs don't put you to sleep --- they take over your mind!  Is Sleepwalker immune to her musical madness?  Check out the cover!                  
Summery

Down in Varick Street Manhattan, Detec. Perez investigates an area where Sleepwalker was at a while back.  All of a sudden the investigation is interupted by O.I.E. Agents.  Perez does not want to deal with them but they give her a detector to find Sleepwalker anyway.

Meanwhile Sleepwalker is uptown watching two people coming out of a car and surrounded by camera men.  It is women named Lullaby and she just married millionaire Harold Cross.  the two enter threw home.

Later that night Sleepwalker shots Harold walking outside to his balcony.  HE jumps off but Sleepwalker catches him.  He brings him to the cops for aid only to be attacked by the crowd which torments him.  Meanwhile Harold's wife Lullaby thanks Sleepwalker and says that she can make people change there views about him.  Sleepwalker accepts and gives her his number.

The next day, Rick Sharidan is having problems on the set of a student film.  As he arrives home he finds a message on his machine hoping it is Alyssia.  It is Lullaby who sings Rick into a trance to meet her.  Sleepwalker comes out of Ricks mind only to find that he is not sleeping.

Meanwhile at the marina Lullaby is in her boat with two men tending to her needs.  Rick enters the boat but this surprises Lullaby.  Sleepwalker comes out demanding answers.  Turns out Lullaby was a teenage babysitter named Felicity Hopkins.  She had the power to sing people to sleep but then in there sleeping state make them do anything.  She got a job with Harold Cross and tranced him to divorce his wife and mary her.  BUt she got bored with Harold and tranced him to jump out of the building until sleepwalker saved him.  

Sleepwalker tries to attack but Lullaby puts him to sleep.  The next day she puts a disguise on him and the two go on a shopping spree which soon turn into heists.  At one Heist she commands Sleepwalker to attack the guards who saw her steal a necklace.  The two then escape.

Back at the downtown precinct, Perez gets evidence from the crime scene using the device linking it to Sleepwalker and Lullaby.  

Menawhile. Lullaby makes Sleepwalker cause all types of chaos in the city.
But moments later Lullaby's effects wear off for they only work for 24 hours.  Sleepwalker then attacks lullaby.

Meanwhile Perez hands over the Sleepwalker case to the O.I.E. who want to destroy Sleepwalker.
name: Sing A Song Of Sin!

description:
A security firm with no concept of civil rights is trying to bring law and order to the streets of New York. And oh yes, kill Sleepwalker. 
 
NOTE: A dream sequence features cameo appearances from several non-Marvel characters.
name: The Hero Within!

description: Paramilitary forces have figured out that Sleepwalker has appeared from another dimension via someone's mind, they just aren't sure who. So they boobytrap the hero to kill his human host upon 'transfer'. The force's attempts have injured many innocent people, which brings Ghost Rider riding by. A brutal battle ensues between the two until GR realizes an innocent life is about to go up in an explosion at any moment.
name: Ghost Of A Chance!

description: Color Blindness, Part 1 of 4.
name: Color Blindnes(Part 1): Blinded by the Light

description: Sleepwalker confronts Spectra, a major new villianess whose lethal powers might cost our alien hero his life!
name: Color Blindness (Part 2):  The Color Of Pain!

description: In order to save the now comatose Rick, Reed Richards and the Thought Police must journey into Rick's mind in a real battle of the psyche!  Guest-starring the Fantastic Four.
name: Color Blindness (Part 3): Journey To The Center Of The Mind
Portals Of Power (Part 3): Doorway To Doom

description: An Infinity War crossover!  Professor Xavier guest-stars as Sleepwalker must battle evil versions of the Beast, Daredevil, and Firestar to stop the Magus from placing everyone on Earth into a trance... forever!
name: Rest In Peace!

description: Cobweb commands the Chain Gang to kill Sleepwalker.
name: Mindfield! (Part 1): Meeting Of The Minds
Mindfield! (Part 3): Mistaken Identities

description: Rick and Sleepwalker are still lost in each other's bodies. This doesn't stop their enemies in the slightest from attempting to slaughter them. Sleepwalker is pinned by Rick's stab-happy girlfriend while various emotional entities torment Rick in the mind-scape.
name: Mindfield! (Part 4): Beyond Life And Death

description: Is Sleepwalker the hero he's cracked to be?  That's the big question our dreamtime hero faces in this double-sized 25th issue, commemorated with an "oil-slick" holo-grafx cover eerily depicting an invasion of Sleepwalkers from the Mindscape!  When an army of Sleepwalkers invade Earth, we discover that everything we have learned about Sleepy's origin thus far is untrue!  Is he the hero we've come to know, or is he really a villian with sinister objectives?  That's the question poor Rick Sheridan grapples with, as he faces the horrible realization that he may have been acting as a doorwayf or an extra-dimensional invasion force!  From here on, Sleepwalker embarks in a whole new direction, as it unravels the mystery of Sleepy's origin.
name: Land Of Broken Dreams;  Falling Asleep;
Dementia Deluxe

description: Sleepwalker's transformation into a murderous, hateful villian is  complete when he goes on killing spree and humans are his target!  Also: Don't miss the return of his most cold-blooded foe, Spectra!
name: Mistaken Realities

description: A new menace has landed on earth. His name is Raditz, brother to Chacarod, a.k.a. Goku. He robs Gohan off his parents and reminds Goku what he was sent to earth for. Can Goku, with Piccolo's help, deal with his dreaded saiyan "brother"?
name: Son-Gokus Bror

description: Raditz has been successfully dealt with, Goku too is dead. Piccolo has sworn to train Goha n. Now Goku's spaceship generates a hologram of the Moon and turns Gohan into a super powered Gorilla(the Ozaru form)! Can Piccolo deal with this new menace? Meanwhile the other Z-fighters are training with Kame. And the dreadful saiyans are arriving...
name: Äventyr I Himlen

description: The saiyans have arrived, and have already started their destructive actions! Can the z-fighters deal with them? Meanwhile, Goku has finished his training and is returning to earth. Can he reach in time to help his friends?
name: Kampen Mot Nappa

description: The z-fighters have been badly beaten. Goku has arrived just in time to save Gohan and Krillin from the saiyan s. Nappa too has been doublecrossed by Vegeta. Now a classic " saiyan duel" is about to ensue. Goku v/s Vegeta! Who will be victorious? Who will have the last laugh?
name: Vegetas Nederlag

description: Lord Cardinale, the current wielder of the Darkness invades Faerie, a land of elves with the help of Royale, a sorcerer. Only a Spawn and the new wielder of the Witchblade stand between them and their vicotry.

The darkest forces imaginable crash together as Medieval Spawn investigates what he believes to be the ultimate battle between Heaven and Hell. Joined by Katarina, the latest bearer of the Witchblade, the two heroes enter into the land of Faerie for the first time. Also in this issue, we learn the real agenda of one Matthew Royale!

In the ultimate showdown to defeat Cardinale and the Darkness army, Royald manages to turn the Witchblade against Medieval Spawn. With the revelation that they used to be lovers, will Katarina be able to prevent the Witchblade from destroying Spawn?

It's the start of Hal Jordan's training as a Green Lantern…and the Guardians of the Universe have selected Sinestro to be his teacher. But Hal's got a problem. He's serving a 90-day jail sentence by day while fighting alongside Sinestro.

Hal Jordan is sent to prison for driving under the influence and injuring someone. En route to prison he sneaks away to stop a bank robbery and arrives back just in time to get strip searched (this time he was wise enough to conceal his power ring). While in prison Hal is framed for the murder of his cell mate. Hal's caseworker Guy Gardner believes he is innocent and attempts to clear him of the crime. Meanwhile on Oa the Guardians of the Universe call upon Sinestro to train Hal.
name: 90 Days (Part 1) 'The Powers That Be'

description:
Hal Jordan's rigorous Green Lantern training under Sinestro's tutelage continues even as he serves his 90-day prison sentence and receives his first mission…to break up an alien alliance that threatens Earth.

Sinestro begins Hal Jordan's Green Lantern training, but finds him to be hopelessly undisciplined. Meanwhile, back on Earth, Hal gets a new cell mate.
name: 90 Days (Part 2): 'Balance of Power'

description:
Another murder in prison touches Hal Jordan's life…but before he can react, Sinestro shows up to continue Hal's training on Korugar, where the new Green Lantern sees another, more frightening side of his tutor.

Sinestro continues training Hal Jordan in how to be a Green Lantern, but while they're off in space, things are going badly on their home worlds of Earth and Korugar.
name: 90 Days (Part 3): 'Power Play'

description:
Katma Tui leads the people of Korugar in a revolt against Sinestro, whose berserk rage can be stopped by only one man—Hal Jordan.

Sinestro and Hal have returned to Korugar to find a revolution. Katma-Tui, aided by the Khunds leads an all out-assault against Green Lantern hegemony. Sinestro goes berserk and start leveling Korugar until Hal stops him. The two flee to space before the reinforcements summoned by Hal arrive. The result is an all out war that pits Lantern-against-Lantern, and when the Guardians of the Universe learn what's going on, they unleash a secret weapon!
name: 90 Days (Part Four): 'The Will to Power'

description:
Hal and Sinestro are hiding from the Green Lantern Corps and the Guardians in the prison where Hal is serving his time, while a prison riot takes place in which inmates have taken hostages. Guy Gardner, a hostage?

Sinestro and Hal Jordan return to Earth, but find themselves in the middle of a full scale prison riot and Willie and Guy are hostages. Meanwhile, the Fists of the Guardians aren't far behind!
name: 90 Days (Part Five): 'The Price of Power'

description:
Sinestro, the renegade Green Lantern, goes on trial, forcing Hal Jordan to decide whether he'll be a witness for the prosecution…or the defense.

The Fists of the Guardians apprehend Sinestro and take him to Oa to stand trial. Tomar acts as the prosecuting lantern and Sinestro acts as his own defense council. Both Hal and Katma are called as witnesses - and Hal begins to question where exactly his loyalties lie!
name: 90 Days (Part Six): 'The Power and the Glory'

description: Bulma, Krillin and Gohan have left for Namek to search for the Dragonballs. Meanwhile Goku has been restored to full health and is also on his way to Namek in a spaceship specially designed for him to help him in training for fighting. Guess what? Veget a too is on his way to Namek! But unbeknownst to all of them, a far more dangerous foe is already present on this new planet...
name: Destination Namek!

description: The seven wish-granting Dragon Balls are in the hands of evil emperor Freeza! To stop him from becoming immortal, Gohan, Kuririn, and their unlikely ally Vegeta must defeat the remaining Ginyu Force, the four greatest fighters in the galaxy. But it doesn't look good... Once again, our outmatched heroes face incredible odds in a fight for dear life and their only hope is hurtling towards them on a spaceship with an interior pressure of 100 G's - the mysterious and strangely changed Son Goku is on his way.
name: Specialtrupperna

description: Goku has just arrived on Namek. Upon descanding he sees the bad plight of his son Gohan, friend Krillin, and Vegeta at the hands of the Ginyu Force. He revives the three of his allies by using Sensu beans, and destroys half of the Ginyu Force.
name: Gestaltväxlaren

description: The former Guardian of Namek has passed on his power and knowledge to a new successor, Dende. Can this small child summon the Dragon to carry out his friends' wishes? Meanwhile a doublecrossed and angry Freeza is on his way towards the group.
name: Son-Gokus Återkomst

description: The z-fighters have put up a good fight, but all in vain. Freeza has transcended into his final form. Vegeta, Krillin and Dende are already dead. Piccolo is hurt severely. Will Goku have enough power in his new Super-saiyan state to defeat Freeza?
name: Superkrigaren

description:
Freeza is restored to full power by his father, King Cold and is coming to earth! Meanwhile, Goku is also returning. The remaining Z-fighters on earth prepare for an inevitable doom. Enter a new warrior- Trunks.

Who is this Trunks and does he have power enough to match Freeza's evil?
name: Freezers Nederlag
